Office of Digital Learning (ODL)
IIT Kanpur
Procedure for Students
1.
The student interested in registering for the ODL placement process for the upcoming placement session
must prepare a Master Resume and submit it by the specified deadline to the Office of Digital Learning (ODL)
during registration of placement. All the proofs justifying each point in the student's master resume need to
be submitted along with the Master Resume.
2.
The student is also supposed to submit a short resume in specified standard format of two pages to ODL
to prepare the student profile booklet.
3.
The student must register for the ODL placement process within the specified timeframe as notified.
4.
Each program should appoint a team of students as a point of contact (POC) from the students' side for
resume verification and for supporting placement. A team consisting of minimum of two Department
Point of Contacts (DPOC), two Industrial Coordinators (IC) and one Social Media Coordinator (SMC) for
each programme is necessary to carry on placement activities. You may choose the team independently
or individuals can fill the “Supportive Involvement Towards eMasters Placement Procedure”
(https://forms.gle/794AUy1WVnUqnsGn7) to form the team. This form has the details of the
responsibilities for these roles. Following the ODL placement team's evaluation of your participation,
you will receive a certificate for the same. The certificates for DPOC may be collected from ODL office
when the student comes for the convocation or will be posted to the address shared by them post-
convocation. The certificates for IC and SMC would be mailed to the students when the students step
down from the post or six months post-graduation, following a review of their performance by ODL. A
minimum of 6 months of association with ODL for a post is necessary to avail a certificate.
5.
Once the name(s) of the POC and the team is decided, ODL will inform the student coordinators and all
the students of the respective programme about the details of all the team members. It is suggested to
build your connections with your senior and junior batches for smooth handover of responsibilities
from one cohort to another.
6.
The outgoing DPOC, at least one month preceding their graduation, is responsible for selecting a
successor and notifying the ODL before applying for institute no-dues clearance. Facilitating a seamless
transition of DPOC responsibilities to the newly appointed individual is a key duty of the outgoing
DPOC, and it is a prerequisite for obtaining clearance of Institute no dues. If the IC or SMC plans to step
down from their position, they must notify ODL at least one month in advance to allow time for a new
IC/SMC to be appointed.
7.
The student would be assigned a time window during which the allotted DPOC would verify the resume.
8.
Once the resume has been verified, it should be informed to the ODL. After getting approval from the DL
office, the students need to submit their application through ODL before the company's deadline for which
they are eligible/interested.
9.
In case any placement-registered students apply to a company independently, they would keep ODL
informed, especially if they get selected.
10.
Students participating in the lateral placement process (facilitated through ODL/PCs/eMasters
Peers), should keep ODL always in the loop, for interviews and any other communications with the
companies.
11.
Following the application, the student must attend all of the company's hiring events (Pre-
Placement Talks / Tests / GDs, etc.).
12.
When a student receives a job offer from a company, either through ODL placement or independently,
within a year of registering for placement, the ODL office will promptly notify and initiate automatic
de-registration from ODL placement for that student.
